18
00:01:59,411 --> 00:02:01,330
ERIKA: That night,
news of the hit‐and‐run

19
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:04,458
spread like wildfire
across Ikebukuro.

20
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:06,084
Everyone was affected by it.

21
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:08,003
I guess that just shows you
how important

22
00:02:08,003 --> 00:02:10,297
Dotachin was to folks,
doesn't it?

23
00:02:10,297 --> 00:02:11,256
[cheering]

24
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:12,591
Well, not to everyone.

25
00:02:12,591 --> 00:02:14,760
A few people were stoked
when they found out.

26
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:17,804
You can ignore
those dirtbags.

27
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:19,264
Everyone knew about it

28
00:02:19,264 --> 00:02:21,266
by the time the news
got to these two.

29
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:23,602
‐ Our Kyohei's in a coma?

30
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:24,770
‐ Yes.

31
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:26,897
He was involved
in a hit‐and‐run.

32
00:02:26,897 --> 00:02:28,398
‐ You're kidding.

33
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:30,484
So what do the doctors say?

34
00:02:30,484 --> 00:02:31,943
Will he make it?

35
00:02:31,943 --> 00:02:33,654
‐ They don't know yet.

36
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:36,615
They're waiting to see
if he'll regain consciousness.

37
00:02:36,615 --> 00:02:38,450
‐ I see.

38
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:41,203
‐ I want to go visit him,
but I doubt the hospital

39
00:02:41,203 --> 00:02:44,414
is going to let me
through the front door.

40
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:47,459
‐ I'm really worried.

41
00:02:47,459 --> 00:02:49,252
‐ He'll pull through it.

42
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:50,754
He's a tough cookie.

43
00:02:50,754 --> 00:02:53,382
‐ It's not him.

44
00:02:53,382 --> 00:02:56,968
You're the one
I'm worried about, Celty.

45
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:58,637
Even if Kyohei comes to,

46
00:02:58,637 --> 00:03:00,555
he's going to be in the hospital
for a while.

47
00:03:00,555 --> 00:03:03,433
What if, I don't know, something
flares up in the Dollars

48
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:05,060
while he's out of commission?

49
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:08,188
Knowing you, you'd try
to help, wouldn't you?

50
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:14,277
‐ Don't worry.

51
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:15,737
Whether he's around or not,

52
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:17,656
I doubt anything's
gonna go that wrong.

53
00:03:17,656 --> 00:03:19,825
It's not like he's their
leader or anything.

54
00:03:19,825 --> 00:03:21,660
‐ I don't know.

55
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:25,664
It's like he and Shizuo
keep people in line.

56
00:03:25,664 --> 00:03:27,290
Shizuo's the Dollars' muscle,

57
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:28,875
and Kyohei's the conscience,

58
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:31,795
dealing with external threats
and internal ones.

59
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:33,296
Kyohei's always hated it

60
00:03:33,296 --> 00:03:35,465
when people called him
the face of the Dollars,

61
00:03:35,465 --> 00:03:37,300
but now that it's
gotten so big,

62
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,927
if some kind of
conflict comes up

63
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:42,722
he's the guy everyone
turns to for advice.

64
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:45,350
‐ Yeah, I guess you have
a point there.

65
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:47,352
‐ [groaning]

66
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:50,814
It'll be fine.

67
00:03:50,814 --> 00:03:52,607
No matter what happens
with the Dollars,

68
00:03:52,607 --> 00:03:55,318
the important thing is you do
what you think is right.

69
00:03:55,318 --> 00:03:57,195
In the end, I don't care

70
00:03:57,195 --> 00:03:59,823
if you piss off
every person on Earth.

71
00:03:59,823 --> 00:04:02,617
I'll always be on your side.

72
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:11,710
‐ Don't worry about me.

73
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:13,879
The last thing I want to do
is screw up so bad

74
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:17,215
everyone's after me.

75
00:04:17,215 --> 00:04:19,718
I'll keep tabs
on Kyohei's condition.

76
00:04:19,718 --> 00:04:22,888
If anything changes,
I'll let you know ASAP.

77
00:04:22,888 --> 00:04:24,890
‐ Thanks.

78
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:29,811
‐ I'll go fix you
something to eat.

79
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:31,146
[phone chimes]

80
00:04:40,572 --> 00:04:42,574
ERIKA: In another part of town,

81
00:04:42,574 --> 00:04:44,242
these guys were
having a meeting.

82
00:04:44,242 --> 00:04:46,536
‐ I hope you're not looking
for an interview.

83
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:49,247
If you are, you should have
made an appointment.

84
00:04:49,247 --> 00:04:51,082
‐ That's not what I'm here,
Mr. Shiki.

85
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:54,586
I hate to bother you
with personal stuff but‐‐

86
00:04:54,586 --> 00:04:56,213
‐ You're not bothering anybody.

87
00:04:56,213 --> 00:04:58,423
I'm happy to help if I can.

88
00:04:58,423 --> 00:04:59,674
‐ Thanks.

89
00:04:59,674 --> 00:05:01,551
‐ Seeing as how you want
to talk to me,

90
00:05:01,551 --> 00:05:04,596
whatever you problem you've got
must be the serious kind.

91
00:05:04,596 --> 00:05:05,764
Am I right?

92
00:05:05,764 --> 00:05:07,599
‐ Yeah, it is sort of.

93
00:05:07,599 --> 00:05:10,477
I‐I need your help
with a family matter.

94
00:05:10,477 --> 00:05:12,562
ERIKA: So he told him his story,

95
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:14,356
about his missing daughter,

96
00:05:14,356 --> 00:05:17,776
about getting texts from her
and not knowing where she was,

97
00:05:17,776 --> 00:05:19,694
and about how
he thought the Dollars

98
00:05:19,694 --> 00:05:21,947
might have something
to do with it.

99
00:05:21,947 --> 00:05:23,615
‐ I get where
you're coming from.

100
00:05:23,615 --> 00:05:25,075
I bet you're worried sick.

101
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:26,743
‐ Do you know anything
about the Dollars?

102
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:29,704
I've been asking everyone,
but no one's talking.

103
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:31,456
‐ I don't know
what to tell you.

104
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:33,458
You think they're a color gang,
but they're not.

105
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:36,211
Just a bunch of office workers,
students and squares

106
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:37,838
who want to belong
to something,

107
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:39,965
not the kind of thing
my outfit keeps tabs on.

108
00:05:39,965 --> 00:05:41,383
Know what I'm saying?

109
00:05:41,383 --> 00:05:44,261
‐ Yeah, yeah,
I guess you guys wouldn't.

110
00:05:44,261 --> 00:05:47,180
But I heard that recently
there's shady things going on

111
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,640
inside the Dollars.

112
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,809
‐ Yeah, well,
it's a big group of people.

113
00:05:50,809 --> 00:05:53,270
It's a cinch there'd be
a few bad eggs.

114
00:05:53,270 --> 00:05:54,980
You can't expect them
to stay in line,

115
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:56,523
'cause they don't got a boss.

116
00:05:56,523 --> 00:05:58,984
‐ Yeah, I know,
but every time I ask someone

117
00:05:58,984 --> 00:06:01,027
who's a Dollar about it,
they won't talk to me.

118
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:03,405
I keep hitting one dead end
after another.

119
00:06:03,405 --> 00:06:05,574
If I could figure out
how to crack their ranks,

120
00:06:05,574 --> 00:06:07,033
I'd find some answers,

121
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:09,578
but I'm not hip to the ways
of the underworld.

122
00:06:09,578 --> 00:06:10,912
‐ Oh, I get it.

123
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:13,039
So here you are
chatting with a gangster,

124
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:15,000
'cause you think
since I'm a gangster

125
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,085
I might be able
to get you in with them.

126
00:06:17,085 --> 00:06:18,920
‐ Yeah, I guess.

127
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,422
‐ I thought so.

128
00:06:20,422 --> 00:06:22,841
I'm gonna hook you up
with a guy in my outfit

129
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:24,467
who's dialed in
to that stuff.

130
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:27,304
‐ Oh, that's great.
Thank you.

131
00:06:27,304 --> 00:06:30,974
I don't know how I'm gonna pay
you back for this though.

132
00:06:30,974 --> 00:06:33,852
‐ The name of this game
is we scratch your back,

133
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:35,312
you scratch ours.

134
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:36,855
That's how you pay us back.

135
00:06:36,855 --> 00:06:38,815
‐ Oh, sure.

136
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:40,609
‐ Do us a favor sometime.

137
00:06:40,609 --> 00:06:43,153
Like if something comes up
and we can use your talents,

138
00:06:43,153 --> 00:06:46,656
you help us out
and we'll be square.

139
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:49,075
‐ Thank you.
That sounds fair.

140
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:50,535
‐ Then let's get
the ball rolling.

141
00:06:50,535 --> 00:06:52,704
I'll call my guy
and set up a meeting.

142
00:06:52,704 --> 00:06:55,999
You know what people call him?
Red Ogre.

143
00:06:55,999 --> 00:06:58,126
Yeah, but these days
his horns and fangs

144
00:06:58,126 --> 00:07:00,170
ain't as sharp
as they used to be.

145
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:02,547
‐ Yeah, I'm okay
with talking to him.

146
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:04,257
I'm in the middle
of something now,

147
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:07,427
so send him
to the bar later.

148
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:08,803
Sorry about that.

149
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:11,806
So this Mikado Ryugamine kid,

150
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:14,851
you sure he's the one
who started up the Dollars?

151
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:16,102
‐ As sure as I can be,

152
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:17,646
but I'm shocked
to say the least.

153
00:07:17,646 --> 00:07:20,065
To think their founder's
from my alma mater.

154
00:07:20,065 --> 00:07:23,318
‐ Heh. Don't give me
the clueless act, info‐broker.

155
00:07:23,318 --> 00:07:24,903
I bet you homed in on this kid

156
00:07:24,903 --> 00:07:27,238
'cause you knew exactly
who he was.

157
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:29,449
‐ If I said yes,
would it make any difference?

158
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:31,743
We both know more
than we're letting on,

159
00:07:31,743 --> 00:07:33,745
don't we, Mr. Akabayashi?

160
00:07:33,745 --> 00:07:36,915
You knew he was the leader
all along, too.

161
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:38,541
‐ Oh, you think?

162
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:40,752
Either way,
I kind of figure this info

163
00:07:40,752 --> 00:07:43,129
was something you'd want
to keep to yourself.

164
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:44,714
‐ Why would I do that?

165
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:47,384
‐ If you kept it a secret,
it might be worth more later on,

166
00:07:47,384 --> 00:07:51,054
but if you played that angle
and someone like me found out,

167
00:07:51,054 --> 00:07:52,597
that would be bad.

168
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:54,057
‐ I wouldn't dream of it.

169
00:07:54,057 --> 00:07:56,101
And honestly,
I'm just not that clever.

170
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:59,312
You'd have to be to keep
secrets from the Awakusu.

171
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:00,522
‐ Cut the crap.

172
00:08:00,522 --> 00:08:02,107
I doubt you'd be
in business this long

173
00:08:02,107 --> 00:08:04,693
unless you had a trick or two
up your sleeve.

174
00:08:10,198 --> 00:08:13,952
The Dollars have gotten so big,
they're like a goddamn city now.

175
00:08:13,952 --> 00:08:16,955
It's only a matter of time
before it goes up in smoke.

176
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:19,165
‐ Oh, you think so?
Why's that?

177
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:21,918
‐ 'Cause there's a firebug
who wants to watch it burn,

178
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:24,337
but there might be others
starting fires, too.

179
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:25,839
And if he's not careful,

180
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:29,467
he just might get caught
in someone else's fire.

181
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:31,302
ERIKA: While that was happening,

182
00:08:31,302 --> 00:08:35,056
Dotachin was having
a second operation.

183
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:37,475
Things looked beyond serious
for him.

184
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:41,730
But all we could do was sit
and wait for it to be over.

185
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:44,149
You didn't get any sleep
last night.

186
00:08:44,149 --> 00:08:45,692
Go home, get some rest,

187
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:47,485
and I'll call you
when he comes out.

188
00:08:47,485 --> 00:08:51,656
‐ No, he's helped me so many
times, so I'll manage.

189
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:53,158
But how are you doing?

190
00:08:53,158 --> 00:08:54,951
You didn't get
much sleep either.

191
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:58,371
‐ Hmm.
I'm still hanging in there.

192
00:08:58,371 --> 00:08:59,914
I hope they are, too.

193
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:01,416
If it wasn't for Dotachin,

194
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:03,501
none of us would be
on the straight and narrow,

195
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:05,628
especially me.

196
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,172
‐ Oh.

197
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:09,257
‐ As long as I've known him,
he's never been the type

198
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:11,176
to turn his back
on someone in trouble.

199
00:09:11,176 --> 00:09:13,386
He's the kind
of nice guy archetype

200
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:15,388
you don't see much
even in manga.

201
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:17,849
Oh, and look at how crowded
this waiting room is,

202
00:09:17,849 --> 00:09:21,519
and you'll get a sense
of how many people he's helped.

203
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:24,355
He can't have visitors yet,
but they keep on coming.

204
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:25,690
What are they thinking?

205
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:28,193
He's in surgery
for Christ's sake.

206
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:31,488
Oh, well, what you gonna do?

207
00:09:31,488 --> 00:09:34,282
‐ So, uh, where's Walker and‐‐

208
00:09:34,282 --> 00:09:36,951
sorry, I forget
the driver guy's name?

209
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:38,369
‐ Doing what they do.

210
00:09:38,369 --> 00:09:40,955
See, Dotachin's more
than a friend to us.

211
00:09:40,955 --> 00:09:42,499
He's also our brakeman.

212
00:09:42,499 --> 00:09:44,084
‐ Brakeman?

213
00:09:50,548 --> 00:09:53,009
‐ Crap, it's starting to rain.
‐ Told you.

214
00:09:53,009 --> 00:09:55,762
‐ Goddamn, this is good.
‐ Huh? Can I try?

215
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:57,430
Come on, give me a bite.

216
00:09:57,430 --> 00:09:59,265
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

217
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:01,518
[tires squeal]

218
00:10:01,518 --> 00:10:03,103
‐ What the hell?

219
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:04,979
‐ You asshole!

220
00:10:04,979 --> 00:10:06,231
‐ You son of a bitch!

221
00:10:06,231 --> 00:10:08,191
‐ Yo, you trying to kill us
or what?

222
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:09,984
‐ Kushi High never changes.

223
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:11,861
You're supposed to be
on your summer break.

224
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:13,905
Do you ever take
your uniforms off?

225
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:15,740
‐ Oh, you got a problem
with that, wise‐ass?

226
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,158
‐ You wanna die or something?

227
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:19,244
‐ Huh, what's up,
you little dick fart?

228
00:10:19,244 --> 00:10:20,537
[overlapping chatter]

229
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:22,122
‐ No way, Togusa?

230
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:23,790
all: Huh?
‐ Hey.

231
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,750
‐ 'Sup?
Yo, show some respect.

232
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,752
He used to go to our school.

233
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:29,754
‐ Oh, shit.
We had no idea.

234
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:30,713
Sorry.

235
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:31,923
both: Sorry, sir.

236
00:10:31,923 --> 00:10:33,967
‐ It's cool.
No harm, no foul.

237
00:10:33,967 --> 00:10:36,469
The reason I'm here
is to apologize

238
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:38,221
for something I'm gonna do.

239
00:10:38,221 --> 00:10:39,430
‐ Huh?

240
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:41,224
‐ What are you gonna do?

241
00:10:41,224 --> 00:10:44,310
‐ I'm gonna kill someone
by dragging him behind my van.

242
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:47,230
You can see how doing that would
ruin Kushi High's rep,

243
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:48,606
can't you?

244
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:51,109
ERIKA: It goes without saying
that some people

245
00:10:51,109 --> 00:10:54,612
had a hard time
sitting around waiting.

246
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:56,406
If I could be out there too,
I would.

247
00:10:56,406 --> 00:11:00,243
Believe me.

248
00:11:00,243 --> 00:11:01,452
‐ I got a problem.

249
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:04,706
One of my best friends
is heading for trouble.

250
00:11:04,706 --> 00:11:06,082
I want to stop him,

251
00:11:06,082 --> 00:11:08,626
even if I have to kick
his ass to do it.

252
00:11:08,626 --> 00:11:10,795
Thing is,
I can't do it on my own.

253
00:11:10,795 --> 00:11:15,633
I hate dragging you into this,
but I really need your help.

254
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:17,969
‐ We got your back, chief,
you know that.

255
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:19,304
‐ Yeah, just tell us
what to do.

256
00:11:19,304 --> 00:11:21,306
‐ Yeah, chief,
we're down for whatever.

257
00:11:21,306 --> 00:11:22,765
‐ Hell yeah.
‐ You're damn straight.

258
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:24,267
‐ Uh‐huh.
‐ You got it.

259
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:27,770
‐ Yeah, chief, we're with you.
‐ All the way.

260
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:30,940
‐ All right, guys, the name
of the person we're going after

261
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,817
is Mikado Ryugamine.

262
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:35,403
He's the leader of the Dollars.

263
00:11:35,403 --> 00:11:38,031
Yatabe should have
been here by now.

264
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:41,576
[door opens]

265
00:11:41,576 --> 00:11:43,286
‐ What took you so long?
‐ It's about time.

266
00:11:43,286 --> 00:11:45,371
‐ Um...
‐ Yo, what's wrong, man?

267
00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:47,165
‐ Um...

268
00:11:47,165 --> 00:11:48,833
‐ 'Sup, Masaomi?

269
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,169
Short time no see or something.

270
00:11:51,169 --> 00:11:54,297
‐ Walker, how'd you know
we were gonna be here?

271
00:11:54,297 --> 00:11:57,175
‐ Are you kidding?
I just followed your boy here.

272
00:11:57,175 --> 00:11:59,677
I figured if you're bringing
the Yellow Scarves back,

273
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:01,888
it's a cinch you'd be needing
your right‐hand man.

274
00:12:01,888 --> 00:12:03,640
I'm all crafty like that.

275
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:04,807
‐ Oh.

276
00:12:04,807 --> 00:12:06,351
Okay then, why are you here?

277
00:12:06,351 --> 00:12:07,894
You wouldn't happen
to be the guy

278
00:12:07,894 --> 00:12:10,230
that ran Kyohei over,
are you?

279
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:13,358
‐ The reason I'm sitting here
waiting for Dotachin to wake up

280
00:12:13,358 --> 00:12:15,526
is so I can call the boys
and stop them

281
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:18,071
before they can
do anything drastic.

282
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:21,491
They're out there right now
looking for the guy who hit him.

283
00:12:21,491 --> 00:12:23,201
‐ They are?
‐ Oh, yeah.

284
00:12:23,201 --> 00:12:25,954
And if they catch the dude
who did it before the cops do,

285
00:12:25,954 --> 00:12:28,748
they'll most definitely
kill the bastard.

286
00:12:28,748 --> 00:12:30,083
‐ [gasps]

287
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:32,752
‐ Heck, if I found him,
I'd kill him, too.

288
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:44,681
‐ What is this place?

289
00:12:44,681 --> 00:12:46,224
It looks like there was a fire.

290
00:12:46,224 --> 00:12:49,018
‐ Halfway through building it,
the owners bailed.

291
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:51,479
Then a while ago,
something went down here

292
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:52,563
with the yakuza.

293
00:12:52,563 --> 00:12:54,440
And since then,
people avoid it.

294
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,068
‐ I guess this place is as good
a spot to meet as any,

295
00:12:57,068 --> 00:12:59,821
but don't you think it's kind
of far from Ikebukuro?

296
00:12:59,821 --> 00:13:01,239
‐ That's the best part about it.

297
00:13:01,239 --> 00:13:03,908
No one's gonna bother us
way out here.

298
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:06,035
‐ Yeah, good point.

299
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:12,041
Well, let's find out
what the Dollars are up to.

300
00:13:23,136 --> 00:13:24,679
‐ Damn, you're fast.

301
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:27,765
‐ In one day, things have
gotten worse in the city.

302
00:13:27,765 --> 00:13:30,393
I bet it's 'cause of
what happened to Kyohei.

303
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:35,648
ERIKA: People who post crap
like that should be banned.

304
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:38,151
Go get 'em, Mikado.

305
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:39,610
Boy's got skills!

306
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:42,572
That's the leader
of the Dollars for you.

307
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:52,707
ERIKA: This right here
is something to worry about.

308
00:13:52,707 --> 00:13:54,459
‐ Come on, Walker, seriously?

309
00:13:54,459 --> 00:13:56,711
Does it look like
I can afford a car?

310
00:13:56,711 --> 00:13:58,629
‐ You got it all wrong,
Masaomi.

311
00:13:58,629 --> 00:14:00,048
I'm not saying you did it,

312
00:14:00,048 --> 00:14:01,841
but what about
someone from your crew?

313
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:04,635
It's possible one or two
of these fine, upstanding gents

314
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:06,429
went rogue behind
the boss's back.

315
00:14:06,429 --> 00:14:09,307
You know, it does happen
in manga and real life.

316
00:14:09,307 --> 00:14:10,850
‐ Yeah, I guess.

317
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:13,186
‐ There's all these rumors
about the Yellow Scarves

318
00:14:13,186 --> 00:14:14,520
getting back together, right?

319
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:16,064
And online it's like the war

320
00:14:16,064 --> 00:14:18,316
between the Scarves
and the Dollars never died down.

321
00:14:18,316 --> 00:14:19,734
So there's that.

322
00:14:19,734 --> 00:14:21,652
‐ I don't think
anyone here did it.

323
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:24,113
But if it turns out
I'm wrong...

324
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:25,490
‐ Then?

325
00:14:25,490 --> 00:14:27,283
‐ Then you do
whatever you have to

326
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:29,827
to make it right.

327
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:33,331
‐ [chuckles]

328
00:14:33,331 --> 00:14:35,124
I'm going to look
for the guy now,

329
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:37,085
but if I find out
it was one of yours,

330
00:14:37,085 --> 00:14:38,961
I'll be back.

331
00:14:38,961 --> 00:14:42,298
It'd be a shame
if Asuna got singed.

332
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:44,258
‐ Oh.
‐ What the hell?

333
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:46,010
‐ That guy's a freak.
‐ Right?

334
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:48,513
‐ Can't believe we let him
walk out after talking shit.

335
00:14:48,513 --> 00:14:50,932
‐ Don't tell me
you guys can't smell that.

336
00:14:50,932 --> 00:14:54,018
‐ What?
[all sniffing]

337
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:56,687
‐ What the hell is that?
‐ Kerosene.

338
00:14:56,687 --> 00:14:58,147
He had a Molotov on him,

339
00:14:58,147 --> 00:14:59,941
and depending on how things
went down here,

340
00:14:59,941 --> 00:15:01,526
he would have used it.

341
00:15:01,526 --> 00:15:03,736
‐ Hey, you know what?
I totally forgot something.

342
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:05,029
[all scream]

343
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:07,031
Masaomi, I don't know
if you heard,

344
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:09,033
but Shizuo is in big trouble.

345
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:10,618
For real.

346
00:15:10,618 --> 00:15:12,745
‐ You can't take
that post seriously.

347
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:14,497
It could just be
someone trolling.

348
00:15:14,497 --> 00:15:16,040
‐ I don't think so.

349
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:18,209
This member's posts have all
been legit up till now.

350
00:15:18,209 --> 00:15:20,711
So it's a good bet
this one is too.

351
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:22,880
‐ Don't tell me you can remember
every single post

352
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,215
made by every member.

353
00:15:24,215 --> 00:15:26,467
‐ Nah, just the ones
that stick out.

354
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:29,053
Anyway, this is good.
‐ Huh?

355
00:15:29,053 --> 00:15:32,473
‐ I'm glad Shizuo got arrested
after he quit the Dollars.

356
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:36,060
Can't have any bad apples.

357
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:38,396
In a way, I'm glad he's there.

358
00:15:38,396 --> 00:15:39,647
‐ What do you mean?

359
00:15:39,647 --> 00:15:41,566
‐ If Kyohei was still
walking around

360
00:15:41,566 --> 00:15:44,235
and found out about what I'm
trying to do with the Dollars,

361
00:15:44,235 --> 00:15:45,945
he'd stop me for sure.

362
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:47,572
‐ There's no doubt about it,

363
00:15:47,572 --> 00:15:49,532
Mikado's slipped a cog.

364
00:15:49,532 --> 00:15:51,450
Was he always this twisted

365
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:55,329
or did he get this way
after we showed up?

366
00:15:55,329 --> 00:15:58,249
Maybe we were drawn to him
because he's broken.

367
00:15:58,249 --> 00:16:00,751
Maybe this is
the best place for us.

368
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:03,421
Now that they're out of the
picture, what will you do?

369
00:16:03,421 --> 00:16:04,589
‐ About what?

370
00:16:04,589 --> 00:16:06,507
‐ Well, with Kadota
in the hospital

371
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:08,676
and that Shizuo guy
locked up in jail,

372
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:10,261
the Dollars will collapse.

373
00:16:10,261 --> 00:16:12,471
They were the ones
people looked up to.

374
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:15,099
‐ Yeah, you have
a good point there.

375
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:17,351
If you have an idea,
speak up.

376
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:20,313
‐ We need someone to take
their place in the Dollars.

377
00:16:20,313 --> 00:16:23,566
The Dollars need a symbol
to represent them, right?

378
00:16:23,566 --> 00:16:24,942
‐ A symbol?

379
00:16:24,942 --> 00:16:27,153
‐ Yeah, someone the whole city
knows by sight

380
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:28,571
but don't know anything about.

381
00:16:28,571 --> 00:16:30,281
A famous person
who everyone knows

382
00:16:30,281 --> 00:16:31,490
is a member of the Dollars.

383
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:33,326
There's one person like that.

384
00:16:33,326 --> 00:16:34,619
‐ You mean...

385
00:16:34,619 --> 00:16:35,912
‐ Exactly!

386
00:16:35,912 --> 00:16:37,288
And I have a feeling
they'd be down

387
00:16:37,288 --> 00:16:39,165
with helping us
clean out the Dollars.

388
00:16:39,165 --> 00:16:42,001
Isn't that right,
Headless Rider?

389
00:16:46,297 --> 00:16:50,218
‐ Wait, Celty?
What are you doing here?

390
00:16:50,218 --> 00:16:52,678
Hey, wait, what's going on?

391
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:54,263
How do you guys
know each other?

392
00:16:54,263 --> 00:16:56,182
I mean, what, are you
friends now or something?

393
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:59,018
When did that happen?
Come on, Celty, say something.

394
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,937
‐ We ran into each other
a little while ago.

395
00:17:00,937 --> 00:17:03,147
I apologized for what
happened at the warehouse.

396
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:07,109
I gave her my email
and she gave me hers.

397
00:17:07,109 --> 00:17:09,654
Help me.
No actually, it's Mikado and me.

398
00:17:09,654 --> 00:17:12,657
Right now we both
need your help.

399
00:17:12,657 --> 00:17:15,618
Yeah, see, what happened
to Kadota is a huge issue

400
00:17:15,618 --> 00:17:16,994
for the Dollars.

401
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:19,580
Without him, we've lost
our most ideal member.

402
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:21,165
Heck, there's talk
about Dollars going nuts

403
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:23,751
and causing all kinds
of trouble across the city.

404
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:25,628
Even Heiwajima's quit us.

405
00:17:25,628 --> 00:17:28,673
So now we need a new symbol
to hold us together.

406
00:17:28,673 --> 00:17:32,009
‐ And you want me
to be that symbol, is that it?

407
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:34,470
‐ Thank God, you understand.

408
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:36,847
‐ No, thanks.

409
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:39,267
The Dollars shouldn't
have a symbol.

410
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:41,978
That's the whole point of it.

411
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:54,115
We're not exactly friends.
Acquaintances.

412
00:17:54,115 --> 00:17:56,534
‐ I had no idea.
How come you never told me.

413
00:17:56,534 --> 00:17:57,910
‐ I didn't mean anything by it.

414
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:00,121
I just wanted to surprise you,
is all.

415
00:18:00,121 --> 00:18:02,039
‐ Well, I guess you got
what you wanted.

416
00:18:02,039 --> 00:18:03,749
So what's up?

417
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:07,086
‐ I came here because there's
something I wanted to ask you.

418
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:08,838
‐ Sure.
What is it?

419
00:18:08,838 --> 00:18:12,216
‐ Mikado, what do you want
to do with the Dollars?

420
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:15,136
‐ I guess I want us to‐‐oh.

421
00:18:15,136 --> 00:18:16,387
[shoes clacking]

422
00:18:22,393 --> 00:18:26,022
[all gasp]

423
00:18:26,022 --> 00:18:29,025
‐ I was hoping
I could join the party,

424
00:18:29,025 --> 00:18:32,445
if that's all right,
Mikado Ryugamine.

425
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:36,741
ERIKA: Earlier that afternoon,
a lady on the run

426
00:18:36,741 --> 00:18:39,410
was on her way back
to her hiding place.

427
00:18:39,410 --> 00:18:43,164
She was on high alert,
the way she always was.

428
00:18:43,164 --> 00:18:44,665
But...

429
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:51,922
‐ [gasps]

430
00:18:51,922 --> 00:18:53,883
‐ Long time no see, Namie.

431
00:18:53,883 --> 00:18:57,136
What, you think we weren't
going to find you?

432
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:59,096
‐ No, I didn't, President.

433
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:02,600
‐ Oh, come on now. Why don't
you call me, Uncle Seitarou?

434
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,935
That sounds much better,
doesn't it?

435
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:06,187
‐ [sighs]

436
00:19:06,187 --> 00:19:07,980
You sold out my father
and the others

437
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:10,608
for the sake of the company,
so don't talk to me like family.

438
00:19:10,608 --> 00:19:13,069
‐ Whoa, we can hash
that out later.

439
00:19:13,069 --> 00:19:15,696
How 'bout we get out
of the rain, first?

440
00:19:15,696 --> 00:19:17,865
‐ Why?
Afraid someone might see us?

441
00:19:17,865 --> 00:19:19,575
‐ Exactly.

442
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:23,913
It would be in your best
interest to come quietly.

443
00:19:23,913 --> 00:19:25,706
‐ Kasane Kujiragi.

444
00:19:25,706 --> 00:19:28,459
‐ I'm surprised and honored
that you know my name.

445
00:19:28,459 --> 00:19:30,920
‐ If you're Jinnai Yodogiri's
secretary,

446
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,963
why are you with my uncle?

447
00:19:32,963 --> 00:19:34,256
[groans]

448
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:36,801
You look so calm,
considering the situation.

449
00:19:36,801 --> 00:19:38,636
Do you have ice water
for blood?

450
00:19:38,636 --> 00:19:41,222
‐ You don't really expect me
to answer that.

451
00:19:41,222 --> 00:19:43,808
[whirring]
‐ [screams]

452
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:51,315
‐ I can put her to sleep,
if you want me to.

453
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:52,441
Just say the word.

454
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:53,943
‐ No, don't bother.

455
00:19:53,943 --> 00:19:55,194
If you put her out now,

456
00:19:55,194 --> 00:19:56,696
it's not going
to help any of us

457
00:19:56,696 --> 00:19:59,156
when we bring her dear
little Seiji around.

458
00:19:59,156 --> 00:20:01,033
‐ Seiji?

459
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:02,368
‐ Just to warn you,

460
00:20:02,368 --> 00:20:04,412
we might have to hurt him
a little bit,

461
00:20:04,412 --> 00:20:06,997
but I think you'll agree
that's the best way

462
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:09,125
to make sure you cooperate.

463
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:13,003
‐ If you lay a finger
on Seiji, you'll regret it.

464
00:20:13,003 --> 00:20:15,589
I swear,
I'll peel your skin off

465
00:20:15,589 --> 00:20:17,299
with a molding plane,

466
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:20,219
dissolve you both
in a vat of acid.

467
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:22,179
I'll take a grater
and scrape at you...

468
00:20:22,179 --> 00:20:24,223
ERIKA: And so on a rainy day,

469
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:26,642
Namie Yagiri disappeared again.

470
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:27,977
‐ [screams]

471
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:32,815
KANRA: Good evening, everyone.

472
00:20:32,815 --> 00:20:34,859
Kanra's back!
Meow!

473
00:20:34,859 --> 00:20:37,027
SHARO: Yo.
CHROME: Good evening.

474
00:20:37,027 --> 00:20:39,613
KANRA: Sharo, you should change
your name to Meowru.

475
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:40,698
Cute!

476
00:20:40,698 --> 00:20:42,825
SHARO: No.
And eww.

477
00:20:42,825 --> 00:20:44,869
CHROME: I'm with Sharo
on this one.

478
00:20:44,869 --> 00:20:46,287
KANRA: Oh, I see how it is.

479
00:20:46,287 --> 00:20:48,706
Two big brutes ganging up
on a helpless girl.

480
00:20:48,706 --> 00:20:50,374
And you call yourselves men.

481
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:53,085
CHROME: Yes, well, we don't know
if you're really a girl,

482
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:54,462
now do we?

483
00:20:54,462 --> 00:20:56,130
KANRA: Hmm, then I'll
tell you something

484
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:59,341
that's going to make you
shiver in fear like little boys.

485
00:20:59,341 --> 00:21:00,968
SHARO: I'm shaking already.

486
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:03,596
KANRA: A biker gang might
go to war with a color gang

487
00:21:03,596 --> 00:21:05,556
in Ikebukuro.

488
00:21:05,556 --> 00:21:07,475
SHARO: Wait, where did
you hear this?

489
00:21:07,475 --> 00:21:08,976
KANRA: You've heard about
the Yellow Scarves

490
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:10,478
getting back together, right?

491
00:21:10,478 --> 00:21:12,438
I think they're doing it
so they can start a war

492
00:21:12,438 --> 00:21:14,023
with the Dollars.
Meow!

493
00:21:14,023 --> 00:21:15,858
Kadota's hit‐and‐run
was them saying,

494
00:21:15,858 --> 00:21:17,401
"Come at me!"
Meow.

495
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:19,737
But have you heard the other
rumor floating around?

496
00:21:19,737 --> 00:21:22,031
SHARO: Hold on, that crap
about the Yellow Scarves,

497
00:21:22,031 --> 00:21:23,574
